comment_regular_data.body:
@justinmk I'm working on removing `relative=""` - it causes many tests to fail in `float_spec.lua` as using `win_set_config` on a float and omitting `relative` currently just keeps it as a float. This has the potential to be a very breaking change. Should I still make that change?

Edit: I've instead made it so that a split is only created if one of `vertical` or `split` is set. So you can still omit `relative` when modifying a window config, but setting `vertical` or `split` will change the config to `relative=nil`.

Leaving the commit separate for now as it's quite large and may still have some issues.
